    • pacemodulator

      int pacemodulator()
      A pace modulator function decides if any of these functions have to be invoked for a particular global-tick. The pace modulator function uses a rand library function to bring randomness in decision making.
      Returns:
      pace modulation

    • disruption

      boolean disruption()
      The disruption function models disruption events happening during radio contact and when message packet transfer is in progress. It uses the rand library function that randomly decides whether a particular message packet transfer should be disrupted or not.
      Returns:
      disrupted

    • results

      void results()
      Computes the performance metrics based on the simulation data. Radio Contact Ratio, Throughput, Collective Throughput will be generated.

    • updateGPSLogSeries

      void updateGPSLogSeries()
      Updates the GPSLog series to be used in the GPS Log chart. This function update the series with the information stored in the buck GPS collar. This data is used along with the Datacenter log to calculate the metrics.

    • updateDataCenterSeries

      void updateDataCenterSeries()
      Updated the Datacenter series to be used for the data center logging. The data relayed by W1 is shown on the Datacenter chart. W1 serves as the wild life data collector who relays the information from the buck nodes to the data center at the end of the simulation or at the end of the day.
